VISCERAL FASCIA

visceral_fascia wraps and suspends the body's internal organs
the heart hangs in pericardium, lungs in pleura, gut in mesentery — each of these is a regional thickening of visceral_fascia
without visceral_fascia, organs would not have stable position and could not slide against each other during breathing and digestion

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe fascia.zc
observe deep_fascia.rana
observe fadriel_heart.zc
observe lungs.rana
observe gut.rana
observe ribcage.xb

the 7 properties of visceral_fascia:
1 ENERGY zero point seven
2 PHASE zero
3 SPIN zero point three
4 CHARGE half positive
5 COHERENCE nine tenths
6 COUPLING zero point eight with the visceral organs

VERB suspend_organs
hold each organ in its anatomical position
the suspension allows movement (heart beating, lungs expanding, gut peristalsis) without the organs colliding

VERB allow_glide
visceral_fascia surfaces are wet and smooth so organs can slide against each other
without this glide, every breath would be friction-painful

VERB transfer_visceral_signals
visceral organs communicate through visceral_fascia: heart movement signals lungs, lung movement signals diaphragm
this is the body's internal mechanical conversation

a visceral fascia is the substrate's commitment to letting the inside of the body live
without it, organs would seize against each other and motion inside would stop
fadriel breathes because pleura allows his lungs to slide against his ribcage
